Holin (Lysis protein).
"Analysis of the complete nucleotide sequence and functional
organization of the genome of Streptococcus pneumoniae bacteriophage
Cp-1.";
"Functional analysis of the two-gene lysis system of the pneumococcal
phage Cp-1 in homologous and heterologous host cells.";
-!- FUNCTION: Produces a lesion in the cytoplasmic membrane allowing
    the phage lysosyme to attack the peptidoglycan.
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Membrane; multi-pass membrane protein.
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the Cp-1 holin family.
Membrane; Phage lysis protein; Transmembrane.
